  "original_title": "\u0b87\u0bb2\u0b99\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc8\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc1 \u0b86\u0ba4\u0bb0\u0bb5\u0bb3\u0bbf\u0baa\u0bcd\u0baa\u0bcb\u0bae\u0bcd: \u0baa\u0bca\u0bb0\u0bbf\u0bb8\u0bcd \u0b9c\u0bcb\u0ba9\u0bcd\u0b9a\u0ba9\u0bcd",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Let's support Sri Lanka: Boris Johnson",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Amid the economic and social challenges the country is currently facing, British Prime Minister Boris Johnson has said that Britain will continue to support the people of Sri Lanka.",
        "The British Prime Minister said this in his message congratulating Ranil Wickremesinghe on his inauguration as the President of Sri Lanka.",
        "British Prime Minister Boris Johnson has praised President Ranil Wickremesinghe's efforts to establish a government that prioritizes finding permanent solutions to the problems faced by the people of Sri Lanka.",
        "He also mentioned that following democratic principles and achieving democratic harmony will lead to the victory of President Ranil Wickremesinghe.",
        "I am confident that you will be able to see progress very soon with the cooperation of the International Monetary Fund. Boris Johnson also mentioned that Britain is waiting to work with its international partners to help Sri Lanka in this matter. (a)"
      ],
